ernatively, the name may arise from the Middle English personal name <i>Harwold</i>, <i>Harold</i> (Old English <i>Hereweald</i>), particularly in Suffolk, where there was also post-medieval confusion with   Hurrell  . These all go back to an ancient Germanic personal name composed of the elements <i>heri</i>, <i>hari</i> ‘army’ + <i>wald</i> ‘rule’, which is attested in Europe from an early date; the Roman historian Tacitus records a certain <i>Cariovalda</i>, chief of the ancient Germanic tribe of the Batavi, as early as the 1st century  AD  See also   Herald  .","English: habitational name from Harrold (Bedfordshire), from Old English <i>hār</i> ‘gray’ + <i>wald</i> ‘large tract of woodland, high woodland’.","Irish: this name is of direct Norse origin (see 1 above), but is also occasionally a variant of   Harrell   and   Hurrell  . Spellings without final <i>d</i> have been adopted as the Anglicized form of the Gaelic <i>Ó hEarghail</i> (see   Harrell  )."]}]},{"name":"Alice","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a variant of   Adelaide  , representing an Old French spelling of a reduced form of Germanic <i>Adalheidis</i>. <i>Alice</i> and <i>Adelaide</i> were already regarded as distinct names in English during the medieval period. <i>Alice</i> enjoyed a surge of popularity in the 19th century and periods of favour ever since. It was the name of the central character of  Lewis Carroll's  Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (  1865 ) and Through the Looking Glass (  1872 ), who was based on his child friend  Alice Liddell , daughter of the Dean of Christ Church, Oxford."],"variants":[{"name":"Alys","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alice ."]},{"name":"Alis","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Alice</b> ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Alice Harrold was born in 1340, in Pembroke, Pembrokeshire, Wales, her father, Sir Richard Harold, Knight, was 40 and her mother, Eleanor Hill, was 31. She had at least 1 son and 1 daughter with Peter Perrot."},"et":{"1340–":"1340–Surnud","1340–Female":"1340–Surnud","1330–1378":"1330–1378","1359–Female":"1359–Surnud","1360–1428":"1360–1428","1300–Male":"1300–Surnud","1309–Female":"1309–Surnud","1359":"1359","1378":"1378","1300":"1300","about 1359":"umbes 1359","1330":"1330","1340":"1340","1360":"1360","1309":"1309","1428":"1428","Pembrokeshire, Wales":"Pembrokeshire, Wales","<Of Rathcoffy, Kildare, Ireland>":"Rathcoffey, County Kildare, Iirimaa","Pembroke, Pembrokeshire, Wales":"Pembroke, Pembrokeshire, Wales"},"fi":{"1340–":"1340–Kuollut","1340–Female":"1340–Kuollut","1330–1378":"1330–1378","1359–Female":"1359–Kuollut","1360–1428":"1360–1428","1300–Male":"1300–Kuollut","1309–Female":"1309–Kuollut","1359":"1359","1378":"1378","1300":"1300","about 1359":"noin 1359","1330":"1330","1340":"1340","1360":"1360","1309":"1309","1428":"1428","Pembrokeshire, Wales":"Pembrokeshire, Wales","<Of Rathcoffy, Kildare, Ireland>":"Rathcoffey, County Kildare, Irlanti","Pembroke, Pembrokeshire, Wales":"Pembroke, Pembrokeshire, Wales"},"fr":{"1340–":"1340–Décédée","1340–Female":"1340–Décédée","1330–1378":"1330–1378","1359–Female":"1359–Décédée","1360–1428":"1360–1428","1300–Male":"1300–Décédé","1309–Female":"1309–Décédée","1359":"1359","1378":"1378","1300":"1300","about 1359":"environ 1359","1330":"1330","1340":"1340","1360":"1360","1309":"1309","1428":"1428","Pembrokeshire, Wales":"Pembrokeshire, Galles","<Of Rathcoffy, Kildare, Ireland>":"Rathcoffey, County Kildare, Irlande","Pembroke, Pembrokeshire, Wales":"Pembroke, Pembrokeshire, Galles","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Alice Harrold est née en 1340, à Pembroke, Pembrokeshire, Galles, son père, Sir Richard Harold, Knight, avait 40 ans et sa mère, Eleanor Hill, avait 31 ans. Elle a eu au moins 1 fils et 1 fille avec Peter Perrot."},"de":{"1340–":"1340–Verstorben","1340–Female":"1340–Verstorben","1330–1378":"1330–1378","1359–Female":"1359–Verstorben","1360–1428":"1360–1428","1300–Male":"130